{"id":17467,"date":"2014-01-04T11:59:14","date_gmt":"2014-01-04T07:59:14","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=17467"},"modified":"2021-08-05T08:26:48","modified_gmt":"2021-08-05T04:26:48","slug":"judge-deeds-not-hearts","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/04\/judge-deeds-not-hearts\/","title":{"rendered":"Umar on Judgment: We judge outward deeds, not inner-states"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn &#8216;Utbah reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, people were judged by revelation in the time of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and the revelation has ceased. We only judge now what is manifested outwardly of your deeds. Whoever shows us good, we will trust him and bring him close. It is not for us to judge anything of his inner secrets. Allah will hold him accountable for his inner secrets. Whoever shows us evil, we will never trust him or believe him even if it is said his intentions are good.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2641<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Sahih<\/i><\/b> (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0639\u064f\u062a\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0623\u064f\u0646\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064b\u0627 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u064a\u064f\u0624\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0630\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0648\u064e\u062d\u0652\u064a\u0650 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0647\u06